{
  "stem": "27390.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that we shouldn't be frightened and the Germans don't stand a chance and they won't be able to defeat the Poles.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The Poles are very strong, patriotic people and they will fight to the end and all kinds of-- and this went on for a few weeks until finally, on, as you know, on the 1st of September 1939, the Germans crossed over the border.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the radio was playing away and saying the Polish Army pounced the German tanks and they shot down so many German planes and they killed so many German soldiers and they-- they penetrated into German territory.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this went on for a few days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In the meantime, we had the air raids.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we were in-- they didn't have shelters, proper shelters, so what they did is they-- they collected a-- what they thought the most safe place in-- in the block in a basement and that's where we stayed all the time while the air raids went on.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The air raids went on like this for-- from Friday to Monday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On Tuesday night, my father was a watchman.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was standing up on the roof seeing that if a fire breaks out to-- he was told what to do, you know?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I-- and there was an air raid on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I didn't undress.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I stood with my father on the roof.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a three or four-story block.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we looked down onto the main square in-- off the Piotrkowska Street, which was the main street in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as we looked down, we could see hundreds of Polish soldiers walking and some of them were bandaged, without shoes, without caps, torn uniforms.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went down quick to find out what's going on.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
